Top level Directories
/boot - files needed to boot the OS
/cdrom - Mount point for CD-ROMs.
/media - Used to mount removable media like CD-ROMS.
/cgroup - Control Groups hierarchy
/dev - Device files, typically controlled by the OS and System administrators.
/mnt Used to mountextrnal file systems
/proc - Provide info about running processes.
/selinux - Used to display info about SELinux
/srv - Contains data which is servered by the systems
/srv/www web Server files
/sys Used to display and sometimes configure the devices known to the Linux Kernel.


Application Directory Structures

/usr/local/crashplan/bin
/usr/local/crashplan/etc
/usr/local/crashplan/lib
/usr/local/crashplan/log




